{
  "texts": [
    "We isolated the following 57 LC and LPLC types: LC4, LC6, LC9, LC10a-f, LC11, LC12, LC13, LC14a1, LC14a2, LC14b, LC15, LC16, LC17, LC18, LC19, LC20a-b, LC21, LC22, LC24, LC25, LC26, LC27, LC28a, LC29, LC31a-c, LC33a, LC34, LC35, LC36, LC37a, LC39, LC40, LC41, LC43, LC44, LC45, LC46, LCe01-LCe09, LPLC1, LPLC2, and LPLC4.",
    "We report individual cell types LC10a, LC10b, LC10c, and LC10d which have been identified in FlyWire, but we do not yet know how the driver lines LC10ad and LC10bc map onto these individual types.",
    "We summed the number of synaptic connections across all neurons of the same type that were either inputs or outputs of one of the LC and LPLC neuron types.",
    "We denoted a connection (Fig. 5b, tick lines) if at least 5 synaptic connections existed between an LC or LPLC neuron type and another neuron type.",
    "We identified 538 presynaptic cell types and 956 postsynaptic cell types."
  ]
}